Sec. 37.14.160.   Duties of the commissioner of revenue.
The commissioner of revenue is the treasurer of the trust fund created in
AS 37.14.110
and shall
(1) in carrying out investment duties under this section, exercise the same powers and duties established for the Alaska Retirement Management Board in
AS 37.10.220
;
(2) deposit the principal and income from investments  into the fund;
(3) invest and maintain accounting records;
(4) provide reports to the board established under
AS 37.14.120
on the condition and investment performance of the fund;
(5)  determine, on July 1 of each year, the monthly average market value of the fund for the five fiscal years preceding the previous fiscal year.

